summary: An Ordinance providing for the payment of the cost and expense of the laying off, opening, extending and establishing of Mary Avenue Northwest, from the north line of the Replat of Lots 8, 9 and 10, in Block A, Hamblet's Acre Gardens, an addition to the City of Seattle, to West Sixty-seventh Street, as provided for in Ordinance No. 35414 of the City of Seattle, by the issuance and sale of bonds of the district created to pay therefor.
